Certain programs (such as \fBlazygit\fP) could create situations where fish would not receive keystrokes correctly, but it is now more robust in these situations (#7853 \%<https://\:github\:.com/\:fish-shell/\:fish-shell/\:issues/\:7853>).
.IP \(bu 2
Arguments longer than 1024 characters no longer trigger excessive CPU usage on macOS (#7837 \%<https://\:github\:.com/\:fish-shell/\:fish-shell/\:issues/\:7837>).
.IP \(bu 2
fish builds correctly on macOS when using new versions of Xcode (#7838 \%<https://\:github\:.com/\:fish-shell/\:fish-shell/\:issues/\:7838>).
.IP \(bu 2
Completions for \fBaura\fP (#7865 \%<https://\:github\:.com/\:fish-shell/\:fish-shell/\:issues/\:7865>) and \fBtshark\fP (#7858 \%<https://\:github\:.com/\:fish-shell/\:fish-shell/\:issues/\:7858>) should no longer produce errors.
.IP \(bu 2
Background jobs no longer interfere with syntax highlighting (a regression introduced in fish 3.2.1, #7842 \%<https://\:github\:.com/\:fish-shell/\:fish-shell/\:issues/\:7842>).
.UNINDENT
.sp
If you are upgrading from version 3.1.2 or before, please also review the release notes for 3.2.1 and 3.2.0 (included below).

